All Progressives Congress (APC) presidential aspirant Asiwaju Bola Tinubu will address the APC caucus in the House of Representatives on March 16, 2022. This was contained in a letter he personally signed and addressed to Speaker Femi Gbajabiamiala, which was read partly at plenary on Tuesday. The former Lagos Governor sought audience with the members to address them on his programmes for the country. Also Read: 2023: Don’t Force Anointed Candidate On Us, Akwa Ibom Youths Tell Gov The Speaker said Leader of the House Alhassan Ado Doguwa will provide details of the meeting later. One of the presidential aspirants of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) Chief Mao Ohuanbuwa is also to meet members of the PDP Caucus in the House around 8.00pm on Tuesday. A notice of the meeting signed by the Minority Leader, Ndudi Elumelu and read by the Speaker showed the aspirant would sell his programme to members ahead of the convention to pick a candidate to fly the party flag.